items.content:
I will show you six new cards that can be sorted in many different ways. I would like to see how many different ways you can sort these cards.

In each trial, make only two groups with three cards in each group. The three cards in each group should be similar in some way.

After you sort the cards into two groups, tell me how you sorted them by typing your response in the box below the card groups. Be sure to tell me how you sorted both groups.
Once you sort the cards one way, do not sort them that way again.
Work as quickly as you can.

This task will focus on how many different ways you can sort six different cards into two groups.

Let’s start with a practice example.
Here are six cards that can be sorted in several different ways.

One way to sort these six cards is into a group of circles and into a group of squares. It is important that I can explain how I sort both of the groups.

Now the cards are sorted in a new way.
The group on the left is sorted by male names, and the group on the right is sorted by female names.
It is important that I make two groups of three cards, and that I can explain how I sorted both groups.

I will show you six new cards that can be sorted in many different ways. I would like to see how many different ways you can sort these cards.

In each trial, make only two groups with three cards in each group. The three cards in each group should be similar in some way.

After you sort the cards into two groups, tell me how you sorted them by typing your response in the box below the card groups. Be sure to tell me how you sorted both groups.

Once you sort the cards one way, do not sort them that way again.
Work as quickly as you can.
